<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The Assistant Director of Payroll and
Pensions, presented the report and made the following points in
introduction and response to questions:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
During the quarter, October to December 2025, approximately 1,800
cases were handled. This was slightly lower than some previous
quarters, which had occasionally exceeded 2,000 cases. The
performance indicators set out in Appendix One showed that
performance had remained consistently high, which was reported as
positive.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In relation to communications, officers reported that they had
continued to engage with scheme members as effectively as possible.
During the quarter, October to December 2025, several retirement
planning courses had been delivered and were reported to be
extremely well attended. As a result, additional courses had been
scheduled for the following weeks and months.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers also advised that academies had been signposted to a
useful online session hosted by the Department for Education, which
provided information on the actuarial valuation process to help
improve understanding of how the process operates. A YouTube link
to the session had been made available for those who wished to view
it.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers also provided an update on standing items, including the
McCloud remedy and the Pensions Dashboard. In relation to the
McCloud remedy, approximately 60% of multiple member records had
been reviewed. These related to members with more than one period
of membership, for example where individuals had left the Fund and
later rejoined, or held multiple employments while contributing to
their pensions.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers confirmed that work was ongoing to ensure all periods of
service were accurately accounted for as part of the McCloud
remedy. In addition, checks were being carried out against the
National Insurance database to identify members who held benefits
in other Local Government Pension Scheme (LGPS) funds, as these
members might qualify for protection where they had previous
service elsewhere.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In relation to the Pensions Dashboard, officers reported that, as
noted at previous meetings, the Fund had successfully connected to
the dashboard infrastructure and ecosystem. This was reported as
positive progress and meant the Fund was ready for the commencement
of national testing.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Although the Government had not yet confirmed a go-live date,
officers advised that six months&rsquo; advance notice would be
provided. In the meantime, work had continued to review and improve
the accuracy of member data in preparation for the dashboards
becoming publicly available.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers referred members to paragraph 2.25 of the report, which
provided a brief summary of the recent Access and Protections
consultation that had been launched and had since closed.
Lambeth&rsquo;s response to the consultation was set out in
Appendix Two.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In summary, the consultation covered changes relating to the four
areas listed in the report, one of which concerned the
reinstatement of LGPS access for councillors. Officers advised that
this was expected to take place around June 2026, which was
reported as positive. It was noted that should this change be
implemented, the pensions team would provide councillors with the
relevant information required to join the scheme, including details
of the necessary steps.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
A member asked &nbsp;...&nbsp; <a href="mgAi.aspx?ID=67129" title=
"Link to view the full item text for item 5., Pensions Administration Performance Report - October 2025 to December 2025">
view the full minutes text for item 5.</a></p>
</div>
</div> 
					
