<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The Assistant Director of Payroll and Pensions
and the Acting Assistant Director of Finance, presented the report
and made the following points in introduction and response to
questions:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers explained that the risks were reviewed prior to each
meeting to identify any changes. On this occasion, there had been
no changes since the previous Board meeting.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers noted that while some changes were likely to result from
the implementation of the governance review recommendations, which
would be detailed in the next report in April 2026, there had been
no changes to the risk register.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers added a clarification for the record in relation to
paragraph 2.4, specifically risk PA22. Officers referred to the
final bullet point in that paragraph, which stated that the risk
rating had changed since the last meeting.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers apologised for the error, explaining that this reference
had been included in the report in error and in fact related to a
change that had been made at the October 2025 meeting, in respect
of the meeting prior to that. Members were therefore asked to
disregard that narrative. Officers confirmed that there had been no
changes to the overall risk ratings during the quarter.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
A member raised two questions in relation to risk PA2, which
concerned insufficient knowledge and understanding of the Pension
Board and Committee in line with legislative requirements,
including the risk of members not undertaking the necessary
training or training not being delivered in accordance with the
Fund Business Plan. It was noted that the risk rating had remained
unchanged since October 2025, and members had previously
highlighted the importance of ensuring that training was completed
promptly.<span style="">&nbsp;</span> The member asked whether this
issue would be addressed before the elections in May 2026, given
that the Council was nearing the end of its term, and how the Fund
intended to ensure that Members of both the Committee and the Board
were fully trained following the elections, particularly
<span class="GramE">in light of</span> the likelihood of
significant Member turnover.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers explained that there had been several changes in
membership across both the Committee and the Board over the past
18&ndash;24 months, which was one of the reasons the risk rating
had remained unchanged. Officers advised that assessments of
training were based on Members&rsquo; completion of the full LOLA
online training package, alongside attendance at training events,
as recorded in the training log. It was noted that enforcing
training requirements was challenging. While minimum training
expectations could be recommended through policy, enforcement was
difficult without a wider Council-level policy on training
regarding this matter. Officers emphasised that this was not a
reflection on individual Members&rsquo; commitment but acknowledged
that securing engagement could be particularly challenging for
non-decision-making bodies such as the Pension Board, compared with
the Pensions Committee.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers further advised that the recent governance review
undertaken by Hymans Roberson had identified the need to refresh
and update the existing training policy. This was not only
considered good practice but also necessary to reflect new
requirements under the forthcoming &ldquo;Fit &nbsp;...&nbsp;
<a href="mgAi.aspx?ID=67130" title=
"Link to view the full item text for item 6., Risk Register Update">
view the full minutes text for item 6.</a></p>
