<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The Assistant Director of Payroll and
Pensions, presented the report and made the following points in
introduction and response to questions:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
The report introduced the new overpayment and underpayment policy
for the Lambeth Pension Fund. <span class="GramE">In light
of</span> recent governance changes and reforms, it was considered
necessary to adopt a dedicated overpayments and underpayments
policy, rather than continuing to rely on the Council&rsquo;s
corporate policies, as had previously been the case.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
The policy strengthened governance arrangements by setting out
clear and consistent procedures for the prevention, identification,
and correction of overpayments and underpayments. It explained how
errors were avoided through robust controls, how overpayments were
recovered in a proportionate manner, and how underpayments were
corrected promptly and responsibly, including the payment of
interest where required.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
It was also noted that much of the practice set out in the policy
reflected existing arrangements; the policy did not introduce new
processes but formalised current practices within a dedicated
policy specific to the Pension Fund.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
A member asked what the average time between the creation of an
error and its detection.<span style="">&nbsp;</span> Officers
explained that this could vary significantly. For example,
reference was made to the transfer of data from one system to
another, specifically the Oracle system. Data migration from Oracle
to the new system had implications for some Lambeth employees, and
as a result, certain issues were identified later rather than
sooner. In some cases, an error may have occurred many years
previously for example, within a deferred benefit statement and was
only identified when the individual&rsquo;s benefits were brought
into payment.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Consequently, officers confirmed that there was no fixed timescale
for the identification of errors. Officers noted that <span class=
"GramE">a number of</span> measures were now in place due to
improvements in systems and the formalisation of processes over
recent years. As a result, current errors were very rare, with
<span class="GramE">the majority of</span> issues relating to
historic errors rather than those arising under current
arrangements.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
A member referred to paragraph 1.1 of the report, noting that the
policy was described as &lsquo;replacing reliance&rsquo; on the
Council&rsquo;s corporate debt policy, rather than explicitly
stating it was &lsquo;replacing&rsquo; the Council&rsquo;s
corporate policy. As a result, it was unclear which policy would
take precedence in the event of a dispute. It was suggested that
the wording be amended to remove the reference to
&ldquo;reliance&rdquo; and to state clearly that the policy
replaced the Council&rsquo;s corporate debt policy.<span style=
"">&nbsp;</span> Officers confirmed that, in the event of a
dispute, the Pension Fund overpayments and underpayments policy
would take precedence. It was also clarified that the reference to
&ldquo;reliance&rdquo; appeared in the report text rather than
within the policy itself.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
A member asked whether, during the McCloud reconciliation exercise,
any additional overpayments or underpayments were
identified.<span style="">&nbsp;</span> Officers confirmed that a
small number of issues were identified. However, the majority of
overpayment and underpayment matters had arisen during the
Guaranteed Minimum Pension (GMP) reconciliation exercise, where GMP
amounts were found to be either higher or lower than previously
recorded, requiring corrective &nbsp;...&nbsp; <a href=
"mgAi.aspx?ID=67131" title=
"Link to view the full item text for item 7., Overpayment and Underpayment Policy">
view the full minutes text for item 7.</a></p>
</div>
</div> 
					
        </td>
