<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The Acting Assistant Director of Finance,
presented the report and made the following points in introduction
and response to questions:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers highlighted key points from the report, which provided an
overview of several matters. In relation to London CIV and the
&ldquo;Fit for the Future&rdquo; transition, it was noted that work
was ongoing to meet the 1 April 2026 deadline, with <span class=
"GramE">a number of</span> interdependencies and associated
complexities.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers referred to recent consultations on new regulatory changes
intended to support the proposed reforms, alongside forthcoming
guidance to underpin those changes. The Fund&rsquo;s response to
the technical consultation, which had closed earlier in January
2026, was attached at Appendix 1. This response primarily related
to two new statutory instruments, which represented updates to
existing legislation to reflect the &ldquo;Fit for the
Future&rdquo; changes.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
It was also noted that a separate consultation on guidance had been
issued to a smaller <span class="GramE">group</span> and, at the
request of Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government
(MHCLG), the Fund had not responded directly but had instead
contributed to a collective response on behalf of London pension
funds. Officers advised that responses to both consultations were
awaited.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In addition, it was reported that the Pension Schemes Bill, which
would largely determine the pace of implementation, was still
progressing through Parliament. <span class="GramE">A number
of</span> amendments and queries regarding the wording of the Bill
had been raised during its passage.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers noted that the governance review update had already been
discussed and confirmed that a further report would be presented to
the Board at the April 2026 meeting. It was also noted that the
matter was expected to be considered by the Pensions Committee at
its March 2026 meeting.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
At paragraphs 2.12 and 2.13, it was reported that in October 2024
officers undertook a review of the Fund&rsquo;s exposure to
companies identified by the United Nations as being involved in
certain activities relating to the illegal occupation of Palestine
by Israel. That review identified a very limited exposure to
companies on the list, amounting to approximately &pound;250,000 of
the Pension Fund.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
It was further noted that the United Nations updated its list in
September 2025, adding <span class="GramE">a number of</span>
companies, bringing the total to 158 businesses across 11
countries. Officers subsequently reviewed the Fund&rsquo;s exposure
to the updated list using Fund valuations as at the end of June
2025. As at that date, the Fund held no exposure to any of the
companies identified.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers confirmed that the Fund would continue to monitor and
assess its exposure following any future updates to the United
Nations list, which were expected to be issued at least
annually.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In relation to the Pensions Committee, it was noted that, in
addition to the meeting scheduled for March 2026, the Committee
also had a further meeting planned in February 2026. This meeting
was intended to consider <span class="GramE">a number of</span>
significant items requiring completion before the year end,
including matters relating to the investment strategy and the LCIV
transition.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
The final point related to &nbsp;...&nbsp; <a href=
"mgAi.aspx?ID=67132" title=
"Link to view the full item text for item 8., General Update">view
the full minutes text for item 8.</a></p>
</div>
</div> 
					
