<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">The Acting Assistant Director of Finance,
presented the report and made the following points in introduction
and response to questions:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
It was reported that performance had been above benchmark for the
quarter, returning 4.7%. There were no significant detractors,
<span class="GramE">with the exception of</span> the private equity
funds, which returned just under 2% against a target of
approximately 10%. Officers explained that this underperformance
was largely due to the maturation of these funds, which were
returning cash, and that performance would improve once new
commitments were made to maintain exposure.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers also noted that there were some deviations in the actual
allocations compared with the strategic allocations. Certain asset
classes were outside the set tolerance ranges, typically plus 4% or
minus 5%, as outlined in the Fund&rsquo;s investment strategy.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers noted that these matters had been addressed as part of the
investment strategy update approved by the Pensions Committee. For
example, as highlighted at paragraph 2.7, the Fund had been
<span class="GramE">underweight</span> in private debt and private
equity and overweight in multi-asset credit. These allocations had
been adjusted through the investment strategy, not to correct
current deviations, but to reflect the Fund&rsquo;s requirements
over the next three-year period to achieve its target discount
rate.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Officers highlighted fossil fuel exposure. It was noted that
exposure had increased over the quarter by just over &pound;3
million in absolute terms, rising from 0.33% to 0.47% of the Fund.
Officers clarified that this increase was due primarily to
valuation changes rather than any active investment decisions.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
A member requested an update on Invesco. Officers reported that the
Fund previously held two Invesco funds: the European Fund and the
UK Residential Fund. The European Fund had been divested in
accordance with Pensions Committee approval, with the sale
concluding in November 2025. The proceeds from that sale had been
received, and the Fund had fully exited its position in the Invesco
European Fund.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Regarding the Invesco UK Residential Fund, officers noted that
further details were considered more appropriate for discussion in
the private meeting.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><b>RESOLVED</b>:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt">1.To note the report,
together with the information in the accompanying performance
report at Appendix One.</p>
</div>
</div> 
					
